# Solar Website Project Structure

## Overview
This is a Next.js 15 solar panel website (Otovo clone) using the App Router architecture with TypeScript and React 19.

## Key Configuration Files
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts (using pnpm)
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with strict mode enabled
- [components.json](mdc:components.json) - shadcn/ui configuration (New York style)
- [next.config.mjs](mdc:next.config.mjs) - Next.js configuration

## Directory Structure

### `/app` - Next.js App Router
- [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Homepage with sections (hero, stats, features, etc.)
- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with theme provider
- [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css) - Global styles and Tailwind configuration
- **app/roof-search/** - Roof search feature pages
- **app/roof-selection/** - Roof selection feature pages
- **app/actions/** - Server actions (e.g., [solar-api.ts](mdc:app/actions/solar-api.ts))

### `/components` - React Components
- **components/ui/** - shadcn/ui components (button, input, etc.)
- Component files follow kebab-case naming (e.g., `hero-section.tsx`)
- [components/theme-provider.tsx](mdc:components/theme-provider.tsx) - Dark mode support
- [components/google-maps-loader.tsx](mdc:components/google-maps-loader.tsx) - Google Maps integration

### `/lib` - Utilities
- [lib/utils.ts](mdc:lib/utils.ts) - Utility functions (cn helper for className merging)

### `/public` - Static Assets
- Images and SVG files (logo, placeholder images, solar panel photos)

## Import Aliases
Use the `@/` alias for all imports:
```typescript
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
```

## Package Manager
This project uses **pnpm** - always use `pnpm install`, `pnpm add`, etc.

## Key Technologies
- Next.js 15.2.4 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript 5 (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui (New York style)
- Motion (Framer Motion) for animations
- React Hook Form + Zod for forms
- next-themes for dark mode
